{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1824a","heading":"Recyclable materials","label":"1824a Recyclable materials","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1824a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/ch28/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1824a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was formerly classified as a note under .section 1811 of this title","Amendments2014—Subsec. (c). substituted “fiscal year 2009 and each fiscal year thereafter” for “each of the fiscal years 2009 through 2013”.Pub. L. 113–76"],"amendments":["Amendments2014—Subsec. (c). substituted “fiscal year 2009 and each fiscal year thereafter” for “each of the fiscal years 2009 through 2013”.Pub. L. 113–76"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Collection and sale of recyclable materials","label":"a Collection and sale of recyclable materials","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1824a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1824a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1824a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Establishment of program","label":"1 Establishment of program","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1824a/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1824a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1824a%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Architect of the Capitol shall establish a program for the collection and sale of recyclable materials collected from or on the Capitol buildings and grounds, in accordance with the procedures applicable under subchapter III of chapter 5 of subtitle I of title 40, to the sale of surplus property by an executive agency.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","num